The President of the United States issued a statement on the meeting of the Interagency Task Force to Monitor and Combat Trafficking in Persons. The statement emphasized the commitment of the United States to the cause of freedom and the eradication of modern slavery. The government plans to use various tools, including law enforcement, victim services, public awareness, and diplomatic pressure, to combat trafficking. The President also highlighted the importance of partnerships with local communities, faith-based organizations, NGOs, schools, and businesses. The cabinet has been directed to strengthen current efforts and expand partnerships to bring more resources to fight against this injustice. The statement expresses confidence in ending modern slavery and reaffirms the United States' support for those committed to this issue.